SimplyMessages
==============

SimplyMessages is a Rails plugin providing a unified success/error messages handling (like those: flash.now[:succes] = 'Yeah').
Based on the message_block plugin by Ben Hughes (http://github.com/railsgarden/message_block).


Requirements
============

Rails version 2.2.2+


Installation
============

git submodule add git://github.com/pjg/simply_messages.git vendor/plugins/simply_messages
git commit -m "Added simply_messages plugin as a submodule."


app/views/layouts/application.html.erb

<%= messages_block %>

By default the messages_block function will display all flash[:success] and flash[:error] messages and all errors for model object associated by name with the current controller (so it will display all model errors for @user model when 'users' is the current controller).

We can also specify the model we would like to display errors for, like this:

<%= messages_block :for => :comment %>

We can also display errors for more than one model:

<%= messages_block :for => [:post, :comment] %>


EXAMPLE 1
=========

controller:

flash.now[:success] = 'Post saved'

view:

<%= messages_block %>

will result in:

<div class="success">
<p>Post saved.</p>
</div>


EXAMPLE 2
=========

users_controller:

@user.errors.add('name', 'name should not be empty')
flash.now[:error] = 'Unable to add user'

view:

<%= messages_block %>

will result in:

<div class="error">
<p>Unable to add user:</p>
<ul>
<li>name should not be empty</li>
</ul>
</div>



